      "content": "北京第二外国语学院学报 ›› 2025, Vol. 47 ›› Issue (1): 73-88.DOI: 10.12002/j.bisu.566\n出版日期:\n2025-02-28\n发布日期:\n2025-04-08\n通讯作者:\n周骁然\n作者简介:\n崔刚，清华大学外文系教授，博士生导师，100084，研究方向：神经语言学、心理语言学和外语教学。电子邮箱：cuigang@tsinghua.edu.cn;基金资助:\nCui Gang(), Zhou Xiaoran(), Ren Yufei()\nOnline:\n2025-02-28\nPublished:\n2025-04-08\nContact:\nZhou Xiaoran\n摘要：\n从早期的双语劣势，到中期的双语优势，再到今天的两种观点并存且相互争论不断，有关双语对认知影响的研究已有百年历史。充分认识双语对认知的影响不仅有助于探讨人类的认知机制，对外语教学也具有重要的理论和实践意义。本文回顾了这一问题的起源，对具体的争论议题进行了归纳，并从执行功能、创新思维和儿童心智理论3个关键方面分析了双语优势的争议现状。我们认为，双语优势之争存在的根本原因在于其复杂性。双语和认知两个概念本身都是极其复杂的，它们在定义、构成要素以及测量方面都存在诸多的不确定性。因此，今后的研究要更多借鉴动态系统理论的基本思路和研究方法，从动态的观点出发，更加全面立体地分析双语对认知能力的影响。\n中图分类号:\n崔刚, 周骁然, 任雨菲. 认知的双语优势之争[J]. 北京第二外国语学院学报, 2025, 47(1): 73-88.\nCui Gang, Zhou Xiaoran, Ren Yufei. The Debate on the Bilingual Advantage of Cognition[J]. Journal of Beijing International Studies University, 2025, 47(1): 73-88.\n| [1] | ABUTALEBI J & GREEN D. Bilingual language production: The neurocognition of language representation and control[J]. Journal of Neurolinguistics, 2007(3):242-275. |\n| [2] | ANTONIOU M. The advantages of bilingualism debate[J]. Annual Review of Linguistics, 2019,5:395-415. |\n| [3] | ARMON-LOTEM S & MEIR N. The nature of exposure and input in early bilingualism[C]//DE HOUWER A & ORTEGA L. The Cambridge Handbook of Bilingualism. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press,2019:193-212. |\n| [4] | BAILEY C, VENTA A, & LANGLEY H. The bilingual [dis] advantage[J]. Language and Cognition, 2020(2):225-281. |\n| [5] | BARAC R, MORENO S, & BIALYSTOK E. Behavioral and electrophysiological differences in executive control between monolingual and bilingual children[J]. Child Development, 2016(4):1277-1290. |\n| [6] | BENEDEK M, JAUK E, SOMMER M, et al. Intelligence, creativity, and cognitive control: The common and differential involvement of executive functions in intelligence and creativity[J]. Intelligence, 2014,46:73-83. |\n| [7] | BIALYSTOK E. Effect of bilingualism and computer video game experience on the Simon task[J]. Canadian Journal of Experimental Psychology, 2006(1):68-79. |\n| [8] | BIALYSTOK E. Bilingualism: The good, the bad, and the indifferent[J]. Bilingualism: Language and Cognition, 2009(1):3-11. |\n| [9] | BIALYSTOK E, CRAIK F & LUK G. Cognitive control and lexical access in younger and older bilinguals[J]. Journal of Experimental Psychology: Learning, Memory, and Cognition, 2008(4):859-873. |\n| [10] | BIALYSTOK E, CRAIK F I M, & RUOCCO A C. Dual-modality monitoring in a classification task: The effects of bilingualism and ageing[J]. Quarterly Journal of Experimental Psychology, 2006(11):1968-1983. |\n| [11] | BIALYSTOK E, & MARTIN M M. Attention and inhibition in bilingual children: Evidence from the dimensional change card sort task[J]. Developmental Science, 2004(3):325-339. |\n| [12] | BIALYSTOK E, & SENMAN L. Executive processes in appearance-reality tasks: The role of inhibition of attention and symbolic representation[J]. Child Development, 2004(2):562-579. |\n| [13] | BLUMENFELD H K, & MARIAN V. Cognitive control in bilinguals: Advantages in stimulus-stimulus inhibition[J]. Bilingualism: Language and Cognition, 2014(3):610-629. |\n| [14] | BOOTON S A, HOICKA E, O’GRADY A M, et al. Children’s divergent thinking and bilingualism[J/OL]. Thinking Skills and Creativity, 2021,41:100918[2021-08-08]. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.tsc.2021.100918. |\n| [15] | COSTA A, HERNÁNDEZ M, COSTA-FAIDELLA J, et al. On the bilingual advantage in conflict processing: Now you see it, now you don’t[J]. Cognition, 2009(2):135-149. |\n| [16] | CROPLEY A. In praise of convergent thinking[J]. Creativity Research Journal, 2006(3):391-404. |\n| [17] | CUMMINS J. The influence of bilingualism on cognitive growth: A synthesis of research findings and explanatory hypotheses[J]. Working Papers on Bilingualism, 1976,9:1-43. |\n| [18] | CUMMINS J. Linguistic interdependence and the educational development of bilingual children[J]. Review of Educational Research, 1979(2):222-251. |\n| [19] | DAHLGREN S, ALMÉN H, & DAHLGREN SANDBERG A. Theory of mind and executive functions in young bilingual children[J]. The Journal of Genetic Psychology, 2017(5):303-307. |\n| [20] | DARCY N T. A review of the literature on the effects of bilingualism upon the measurement of intelligence[J]. The Pedagogical Seminary and Journal of Genetic Psychology, 1953(1):21-57. |\n| [21] | DE VRIES H B, & LUBART T I. Scientific creativity: Divergent and convergent thinking and the impact of culture[J]. The Journal of Creative Behavior, 2019(2):145-155. |\n| [22] | DIAMOND A. Executive functions[J]. Annual Review of Psychology, 2013,64:135-168. |\n| [23] | DIAZ V, & FARRAR M J. The missing explanation of the false-belief advantage in bilingual children: A longitudinal study[J/OL]. Developmental Science, 2018(4):e12594[2019-09-10]. https://doi.org/10.1111/desc.12594. |\n| [24] | DICK A S, GARCIA N L, PRUDEN S M, et al. No evidence for a bilingual executive function advantage in the ABCD study[J]. Nature Human Behaviour, 2019(7):692-710. |\n| [25] | DIJKSTRA T. Bilingual visual word recognition and lexical access[C]//KROLL J F & DE GROOT A M B. Handbook of Bilingualism: Psycholinguistic Approaches. New York: Oxford University Press,2005:179-201. |\n| [26] | FAN S P, LIBERMAN Z, KEYSAR B, et al. The exposure advantage: Early exposure to a multilingual environment promotes effective communication[J]. Psychological Science, 2015(7):1090-1097. |\n| [27] | FLEITH D D S, RENZULLI J S, & WESTBERG K L. Effects of a creativity training program on divergent thinking abilities and self-concept in monolingual and bilingual classrooms[J]. Creativity Research Journal, 2002(3-4):373-386. |\n| [28] | GASS S M, & SELINKER L. Second Language Acquisition: An Introductory Course[M]. 3rd Ed. Routledge, 2008. |\n| [29] | GOETZ P J. The effects of bilingualism on theory of mind development[J]. Bilingualism: Language and Cognition, 2003(1):1-15. |\n| [30] | GREEN D W, & ABUTALEBI J. Language control in bilinguals: The adaptive control hypothesis[J]. Journal of Cognitive Psychology, 2013(5):515-530. |\n| [31] | HAN S & LEE K. Cognitive and affective perspective-taking ability of young bilinguals in South Korea[J]. Child Studies in Asia-Pacific Contexts, 2013(1):69-80. |\n| [32] | HOLTZMAN W H Jr. Divergent Thinking as a Function of the Degree of Bilingualism of Mexican-American and Anglo Fourth-Grade Students[D]. Austin:University of Texas at Austin,1980. |\n| [33] | JACOBS J F, & PIERCE M L. Bilingualism and creativity[J]. Elementary English, 1966(5):499-503. |\n| [34] | KHARKHURIN A V. Sociocultural differences in the relationship between bilingualism and creative potential[J]. Journal of Cross-Cultural Psychology, 2010(5-6):776-783. |\n| [35] | KHARKHURIN A V. Language mediated concept activation in bilingual memory facilitates cognitive flexibility[J/OL]. Frontiers in Psychology, 2017,8:1067[2018-06-28]. https://doi.org/10.3389/fpsyg.2017.01067. |\n| [36] | KOUSAIE S, & PHILLIPS N A. Conflict monitoring and resolution: Are two languages better than one? Evidence from reaction time and event-related brain potentials[J]. Brain Research, 2012,1446:71-90. |\n| [37] | KOVÁCS A M. Early bilingualism enhances mechanisms of false-belief reasoning[J]. Developmental Science, 2009(1):48-54. |\n| [38] | KYUCHUKOV H, & DE VILLIERS J. Theory of mind and evidentiality in Romani-Bulgarian bilingual children[J]. Psychology of Language and Communication, 2009(2):21-34. |\n| [39] | LANDRY R G. A comparison of second language learners and monolinguals on divergent thinking tasks at the elementary school level[J]. Modern Language Journal, 1973(1-2):10-15. |\n| [40] | LANDRY R G. The enhancement of figural creativity through second language learning at the elementary school level[J]. Foreign Language Annals, 1974(5):111-115. |\n| [41] | LARSEN-FREEMAN D, & CAMERON L. Complex Systems and Applied Linguistics[M]. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2008. |\n| [42] | LEE H, & KIM K H. Relationships between bilingualism and adaptive creative style, innovative creat"
